WEBVTT

00:11:58.931 --> 00:12:03.152
what somebody ends up with is
a job that behaviorally is executed,

00:12:03.176 --> 00:12:06.835
and sort of looks different
than it would have been when they started.

00:12:06.859 --> 00:12:09.111
AG: Instead of just accepting
a job description

00:12:09.135 --> 00:12:10.780
that was written for someone else,

00:12:10.804 --> 00:12:13.955
you customize the job to fit
your strengths, values and interests.

00:12:14.293 --> 00:12:16.596
You become an active architect
of your own work.

00:12:17.021 --> 00:12:21.826
AW: We were studying people who clean
hospital rooms as their job.

00:12:21.850 --> 00:12:25.310
AG: The hospital cleaners
were working in pretty rigid jobs,

00:12:25.334 --> 00:12:27.484
but that didn't stop them
from taking on tasks

00:12:27.508 --> 00:12:29.810
that weren't originally
part of their roles.

00:12:29.834 --> 00:12:33.545
There was one cleaner who would go
